div.div:
Different Partners may have different data schema even using same data representation xml/json.
Example
Partner 1 Partner 2
user = user =
{ {
"name" : "ABC", "userName" : "ABC",
addLine1: "aaa", "address" :
addLine2 : "bbb", {
"city" : "xyz". "addLine1" : "aaa"
} .......
}}
Partner1 use "name" but Partner2 schema is having "userName" and Partner1 use flat structure to represent address , but Partner2 is having one more hierarchy. So different parser class are required for different partners.
Whenever new Parser need to be added, Either via Blue-Green deployment phase out old containers and deploy new containers having new Parsers.
OR
A source and target data model attribute mapping can be represented in HashMap<String,List> where a generic parser can be designed to do the required conversions.
